<section id="Highlighting">

	<h2>Highlighting</h2>

	<p>Create rules based on your list titles, and apply the effects you want. For example, you could turn a list red if its title is “Things to do today”. Or you could make it faded if the title contains the words “done” or “trash”.</p>

	<header id="RulesTableHeader">
		<h3>Rules</h3>
		<button class="mod-primary" id="NewRuleButton">Add Rule</button>
	</header>

	<table class="highlighting-table">
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th colspan="2">Rule</th>
				<th>List title</th>
				<th>Colour</th>
				<th colspan="2">More options</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody></tbody>
	</table>

	<details>
		<summary>Notes</summary>
		<dl>
			<dt>Text matching</dt>
			<dd>All text matching is case-insensitive, e.g. TODO is the same as todo. Only whole words are matched, e.g. “doing” will only match the whole word “doing”. It will not match “undoing” or “#doing”.</dd>
			<dt>Order</dt>
			<dd>Rules are applied in the order they appear above, from top to bottom; the first matching rule will be applied. You can reorder the rules by dragging the left hand side.</dd>
			<dt>List title <b><i>is</i></b></dt>
			<dd>This field should contain entire titles. The rule will be applied if the <strong>entire</strong> title text matches one of these titles. This is useful if you share a board with colleagues who do not use this extension and want to apply a rule to specific lists without cluttering up titles with text or hashtags.</dd>
			<dt>List title <b><i>contains</i></b></dt>
			<dd>This field should contain parts of titles. The rule will be applied if <strong>part of</strong> the title text matches, i.e. if the title text contains this. This is useful if you want to use hashtags (e.g. #todo) or you wish to match lists with similar names, e.g. “Things to do”, “To do list”, “Things to do this week”.</dd>
			<dt>More options: <b>strikethrough</b></dt>
			<dd>This option puts a line through all text on the list</dd>
			<dt>More options: <b>greyscale</b></dt>
			<dd>This option turns all colour on lists to grey</dd>
			<dt>More options: <b>other lists</b></dt>
			<dd>When a list matches a rule with the “Other list” options turned on, List Highlighter will look for any lists on the board that do not match any rules. It will then apply the rule you specify to these lists. For example, you could have “To do” lists highlighted red, then apply a “Low importance” rule to the other lists on the board.</dd>
		</dl>
	</details>

	<h3>Other options</h3>

	<div class="standard-options">
		<option-widget>
			<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="HighlightHideHashtags" name="HighlightHideHashtags">
			<label for="HighlightHideHashtags">
				Hide hashtags
			</label>
		</option-widget>
		<div>
			<p>Hide hashtags in list headers</p>
			<p>If this is checked, hashtags will be hidden when you are not editing the list title</p>
			<p>Default: on</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="standard-options">
		<option-widget>
			<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="HighlightUndimOnHover" name="HighlightUndimOnHover">
			<label for="HighlightUndimOnHover">
				Un-dim on hover
			</label>
		</option-widget>
		<div>
			<p>Un-dim dimmed lists on mouse over</p>
			<p>If you’ve made lists less visible (more transparent) as part of a highlighting rule, switching this setting on will un-dim them when the mouse cursor hovers over</p>
			<p>Default: on</p>
		</div>
	</div>

</section>

<template id="RuleTrTemplate">
	<tr data-rule="">
		<td class="dragger-mcswagger">
			<span class="grippy"></span>
		</td>
		<th class="highlighting-enable-column" scope="row">
			<strong class="highlighting-modal-trigger" data-form="RuleName" data-key="name"></strong>
			<option-widget class="highlighting-option-widget">
				<input type="checkbox" id="" name="" >
				<label for=""></label>
			</option-widget>
		</th>
		<td class="highlighting-title-text">
			<div>
				<table class="highlighting-title-text">
					<tr>
						<th scope="row">is:</th>
						<td class="highlighting-modal-trigger" data-form="TitleTextIs" data-key="is"></td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th scope="row">contains:</th>
						<td class="highlighting-modal-trigger" data-form="TitleTextContains" data-key="contains"></td>
					</tr>
				</table>
			</div>
		</td>
		<td class="highlighting-style-column">
			<div>
				<color-chooser class="highlighting-modal-trigger" data-form="ListHighlightColor">
					<color-indicator class="mod-light-background"></color-indicator>
				</color-chooser>
			</div>
		</td>
		<td class="highlighting-more-options highlighting-modal-trigger" data-form="MoreOptions">
			<div>
				{{!-- <button class="link-appearance">More options</button> --}}
				<span class="highlighting-more-options-icon highlighting-more-options-strikethrough" title="Strikethrough">S</span>
				<span class="highlighting-more-options-icon highlighting-more-options-grayscale" title="Grayscale">G</span>
				<span class="highlighting-more-options-icon highlighting-more-options-unmatched" title="Other lists">O</span>
			</div>
		</td>
		<td class="highlighting-delete-column">
			<button class="link-appearance mod-delete">Delete</button>
		</td>
	</tr>
</template>
